Scripts to ship:
- `scripts/install.sh`: idempotent install and verify only.
- `scripts/doctor.sh`: report Node/npm/Figma/binaries/ports/daemon/token state without changing anything.
- `scripts/connect-safe.sh`: guided safe plugin connect; refuses to patch.
- `scripts/connect-yolo.sh`: requires an explicit confirmation flag such as `--i-understand-this-patches-figma`.
- `scripts/daemon.sh`: wrapper for status/start/diagnose/restart/reconnect.
- `scripts/unpatch.sh`: runs `figma-cli unpatch` and reports next steps.
- `scripts/print-utcp-snippets.sh`: prints optional Code Mode snippets only; does not edit `.utcp_config.json`.

Script design should follow the Chrome installer’s check/install/verify/report pattern. Source: `.opencode/skills/mcp-chrome-devtools/scripts/install.sh:314-372`, `:374-395`.

### Failure modes & troubleshooting table
| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `figma-cli: command not found` | Not installed, npm global bin missing from PATH, or npm latest installed only `figma-ds-cli` | Check `npm config get prefix`; install pinned `figma-ds-cli@1.2.0`; verify both bins; use repo fallback if needed |
| `figma-ds-cli` exists but `figma-cli` missing | npm `latest=1.0.0` binary mismatch from prior research | Reinstall pinned `1.2.0`; if still missing, install from upstream repo outside this repo |
| Node version error | Node `<18` | Install Node `>=18`; rerun installer |
| Figma Desktop not found | Figma not installed in `/Applications` or user Applications | Install Figma Desktop or pass documented custom path if script supports it |
| Figma not running/open file missing | Connect requires Figma Desktop with a file open | Open Figma Desktop and the target file, then retry |
| Safe connect does not work | FigCli plugin not imported/open | Import `plugin/manifest.json` once and keep Plugins → Development → FigCli open |
| Yolo patch failed | Permissions, Full Disk Access, admin requirement, app bundle changed | Prefer safe mode; grant permission only if user accepts; rollback with `figma-cli unpatch` |
| Figma update broke yolo connect | App update replaced or invalidated patched `app.asar` | Run `figma-cli unpatch`, update/reinstall Figma, then reconnect or switch to safe mode |
| Daemon `Unauthorized` | Token mismatch or stale daemon state | Run `figma-cli daemon diagnose`, then `figma-cli daemon restart` |
| Daemon not reachable on `3456` | Daemon idle-exited, crashed, or port conflict | `figma-cli daemon status`; start/restart; inspect port owner before stopping anything |
| Port `9222` conflict | Another CDP browser is already running | Identify process owner; stop only after confirmation; retry connect |
| Port `3845` conflict | Official desktop MCP server disabled or occupied | In Figma Desktop, enable desktop MCP server; inspect port owner; retry |
| Official remote MCP OAuth/catalog failure | Client not catalog-approved, OAuth not completed, plan/seat limits | Use Figma-supported client path or mcp-remote bridge; confirm plan/seat/write permissions |
| Official MCP write fails | User lacks Full seat or file permission | Use read-only tools or ask a Full-seat user to perform write |
| Code Mode variable not found | `.env` uses `FIGMA_API_KEY` instead of `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` | Rename to prefixed form and restart Code Mode. Source: `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/references/configuration.md:560-599` |
| Tools missing in Code Mode | Config missing, disabled, invalid manual name, server failed to start | Check `.utcp_config.json`, restart Code Mode, run `list_tools()` and `tool_info()`. Source: `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/references/configuration.md:641-655` |

### Confidence + unknowns
Confidence: high for the local pattern recommendations and Code Mode config shape because all requested local reads succeeded.

Unknowns:
- Exact upstream repo URL for silships figma-cli should be resolved from `npm view figma-ds-cli@1.2.0 repository.url` before encoding it in a script.
- Direct Code Mode HTTP transport for official Figma MCP is unproven in this repo; the conservative path is `mcp-remote` over stdio.
- Exact official Figma MCP tool names and write annotations must be verified with live `list_tools()` before documenting callable names or safety classes.
- I did not run install commands, mutate config, or test external network/OAuth because the request was read-only.
